reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I received these today and have already put them up. They come with everything you need including quality hardware which is a huge bonus. They're simple but look quite nice. I wouldn't say they're heavy duty but are definitely sturdy and I may even buy some for another room in my house! Definitely worth the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Honestly, I bought the shelves because I need them but I ended up with nice shelves.I mean, they are very easy to assemble and the quality of the material is good. Besides if you are looking for small shelves, this one I will recommended because they hold a lot and they are very good

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very Cute Shelves
reviews.reviewText: Okay, let’s first start with assembly and installation. The shelves are handmade, can hold up to 40lbs and are just cute. However, they do feel brittle while putting the screws through so you’ll want to gently apply them. The drywall screws or whatever my fiance told me they were called, are awful. They break SO easily. I think nearly half of them broke while being inserted to the wall. They still worked, but broke.Other than that, these shelves are so cute. They’re pretty sturdy and I enjoy how simple they are. You can add different decorations and stuff to really style your own fit. I decided to do this zig zag style (idk what it’s called, don’t come for me). They do make my house prettier and I am pretty grateful for that. In the end I did think it was worth it!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not for heavy use
reviews.reviewText: We absolutely love that you can use each shelf in a different room, all together, staggered, straight however!! They’re beautiful and looked handmade too!! We used half around our sons room and half in our daughters room and one in my hallway! All from this one purchase ❤️ also the metal stands underneath you can make them look like I did or for more support heavier items flip them around (hard to explain but it’s in the directions if you purchase them)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the color
reviews.reviewText: Love the color. They are very light. Easy to install.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I am well pleased. Very affordable, and surprised of the great quality. All hardware was included. I’ll be using these to extend the debt of my window sills, to display my candles for the Christmas holidays. Very happy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Simple design & materials. Boards were straight and not warped.. surprisingly.....buy your own anchors! I needed to use the drywall screws. Half of them cracked & crumbled into pieces. Cheap plastic. Go to the hardware store and buy a box of drywall screw anchors...you will thank me!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, but gets the job done
reviews.reviewText: The shelves are quite light, but they were relatively easy to install, and they seem pretty sturdy. They come with all of the hardware that you need for installation, and you can put them up pretty much anywhere.
